column3:
@willcl-ark 
> It means that if `brew` is installed but brew's `sqlite` is not, then `brew --prefix sqlite` will still return where it _would_ install it, and having this path added to the Makefile accordingly.

I think the code in this PR handles this case fine, as it actually adds a non-existent path to the `PKG_CONFIG_PATH`, that in turn effectively is noop, right?
